# Git commits — no co-author trailers

When creating commits for this repository:

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by:` lines or any co-author / trailer metadata to commit messages.
- Do **not** use `git commit --trailer` (or similar) to attach co-author information.
- Write only the human-authored commit message the user requested.

If a commit hook strips co-author text, do not re-add it.
